    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <h4>Where can I find my bike's serial number?</h4>
    <p>Most manufacturer's serial numbers are located on the underside of the bracket where the two pedal cranks meet. If there isn't a serial number there, you can check the head tube where the handlebars are, the seat tube, the top of the crank, or near the rear wheel mount.</p>
    <p>If you're still not sure where it is, check with the bike manufacturer for the location.</p>
    <h4>Where can I report a theft?</h4>
    <p>Always report a crime to the local authorities. There are <%= link_to "police in almost every town", "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_law_enforcement_agencies_in_Vermont" %> in Vermont.</p>
    <p>If you have your bike regisered with Safe Spokes VT you should also mark that record as stolen so that if someone tries to sell it to a shop the bike shop can see that it was stolen.</p>
