      <ol>
        <li>
          <h4><strong>Always</strong> lock your bike.</h4>
          <p>Many bikes are easily stolen because they are not locked up. If possible, lock up and store your bike inside. If you're out in public, park your bike on highly trafficked main streets.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <h4>Use a lock that is strong and unbreakable.</h4>
          <p>Lightweight chain or cable locks are easily cut. Your lock should fit around your frame and front wheel so it's hard to remove.</p>
        </li>
